<verse style="v" number="43" />Moreover, when-supposing the unclean spirit may-come-out from of{the man} it-is-being-come-through through of{waterless places} seeking rest and is_not_discovering.
<verse style="v" number="44" />Then it-is-saying, &quot;Into the house of{me} I-will-upon-turn whence I-come-out&quot; and, come[ing], is-discovering being-vacant, having-been-swept, and having-been-arranged/ordered.
