<verse style="v" number="23" />Moreover, the upon the land, the good, sown, the-same is-being the hearing the word and putting-together, who at-this-juncture is-carrying-fruit and is-making on-one-hand the hundred, on-the-other-hand the sixty, on-the-another-hand the thirty.&quot;
<verse style="v" number="24" />He-places-beside another parable to{same}, saying, &quot;The kingdom of{the heavens} is-likened to{[a] man sow[ing]} good sow-effect in to{the field} of{same}.
